  "title": "3 X Draftsman(West 5 days work)",
  "description": "<h3>Job Vacancy: Draftsman</h3><h3>Industry: Construction</h3><h3>Work Location: Boon Lay, Singapore</h3><p>⸻</p><h3>Salary</h3><p>SGD 3,600 – SGD 4,500</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Working Hours</h3><p>Monday – Friday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Monthly Rest Days</h3><p>8 days</p><p>⸻</p><h3>About the Company</h3><p><u>The employer is a construction company involved in building and infrastructure projects, supporting architectural and engineering works through detailed technical drawings and coordination.</u></p><p>⸻</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Review project specifications, technical descriptions, and construction drawings</p></li><li><p>Prepare, coordinate, and update architectural and engineering drawings</p></li><li><p>Submit construction drawings, as-built drawings, and material approvals</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with architects, engineers, and subcontractors to resolve technical issues</p></li><li><p>Liaise with subcontractors to ensure timely submission and approval of drawings</p></li><li><p>Support project teams to ensure drawings align with project schedules and requirements</p></li></ul><p>⸻</p><h3>Job Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Bachelor’s Degree in a relevant field</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>2–3 years of relevant drafting experience</strong></p></li><li><p>Proficient in <strong>CAD drafting software</strong></p></li><li><p>Experience in architectural drafting is preferred</p></li><li><p>Good coordination and communication skills</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently and as part of a project team</p></li></ul><p>⸻</p><h3>Benefits</h3><p>Employment terms and benefits in accordance with Ministry of Manpower (MOM) regulations</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Contract</h3><p>Not specified</p><p>⸻</p><h3>Interview Method</h3><p>Video interview or On-site interview</p>",
